overview: Simon Chan has returned to his hometown after many years training in a faraway martial arts temple. He is a born hero, defender of the weak and champion of the honest people of Cabramatta... Well, not really. For Simon, it's only a matter of time before everyone discovers he's just an ordinary guy, because Simon has a secret. Whilst everyone thinks he was training at a legendary martial arts school in Beijing, the truth is Simon was at Marshall's Art School, in Melbourne. Now back in Cabramatta, armed with a fistful of pastels and a crippling sense of obligation, Simon knows that eventually the truth will hurt... literally. He could lose his life - or worse - disappoint his mother. The world Simon returns to is familiar yet oddly different to the Cabramatta you may know. It's a mix of Asian traditions, absurd superstition and colourful contradictions. A world where brutal gangs terrorise the community with violence and bad karaoke singing; where a magical duck recipe can cast a horny spell and where pirated DVD's are the new crack cocaine. In this town, evil spirits attack nail-and-beauty parlours, council debates are settled via K-Pop dance battles and car parking spots are more valuable than gold. The only thing that stands against all this craziness is Simon. When the ferocious gang leader/karaoke singer Kai Le threatens to destroy his mother's beauty parlour-cum-DVD shop, Simon is joined by his two best friends: Egg, a quick-buck entrepreneur and Petal, a groin-kicking kung fu girl. But can they really protect Simon's family from the Kylie Minogue obsessed gang lord? Will they uncover the corrupt Mayo's secret plan for the town? And can Simon keep his mind off the mayor's daughter for long enough to be (or at least pretend to be) the person everyone thinks he is? Cabramatta needs a hero. Instead they got Simon, Egg and Petal. Welcome to Maximum Choppage, a painfully funny 6 x 30 min comedy series.
name: Maximum Choppage

overview:
British expert gem hunter Guy Clutterbuck has assembled a crack team of miners, from around the globe to source the world’s most precious gems. 

But Guy wants to do it the right way, his plan is to find small scale artisanal mines that have minimal impact on the environment and treat their workers fairly. 

Then he will send his team to help the local mine source and produce gems in a more efficient manner, and most importantly forge a lasting relationship with clients that will make them preferred suppliers in the future. 

It’s a risky business plan, but Guy hopes his 30 years’ experience will give him the business edge to make it a success! 

In this brand new series Guy travels to the mountain top emerald mines of the Chivor district in Colombia in search of a rare crystal clear Chivor emerald, to Madagascar in search of seven sapphires each a different colour, and to the emerald mines of Zambia. 

It’s a lucrative business, but Guy has a tough job on his hands to make a profit whilst educating locals on sustainable gem hunting to make the most of their resources.
name: Mine Kings
